.TH TANH 3 2010-09-20 ""  "Linux Programmerz Manual"
.SH NAME
tanh, tanhf, tanhl \- hyperbolic tangent function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <math.h>
.sp
.BI "double tanh(double " x );
.br
.BI "float tanhf(float " x );
.br
.BI "long double tanhl(long double " x );
.fi
.sp
Link wit \fI\-lm\fP.
.sp
.in -4n
Feature Test Macro Requirements fo' glibc (see
.BR feature_test_macros (7)):
.in
.sp
.ad l
.BR tanhf (),
.BR tanhl ():
.RS 4
_BSD_SOURCE || _SVID_SOURCE || _XOPEN_SOURCE\ >=\ 600 || _ISOC99_SOURCE ||
_POSIX_C_SOURCE\ >=\ 200112L;
.br
or
.I cc\ -std=c99
.RE
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR tanh ()
function returns tha hyperbolic tangent of
.IR x ,
which
is defined mathematically as:
.nf

    tanh(x) = sinh(x) / cosh(x)
.fi
.SH RETURN VALUE
On success, these functions return tha hyperbolic tangent of
.IR x .

If
.I x
is a NaN, a NaN is returned.

If
.I x
is +0 (\-0), +0 (\-0) is returned.

If
.I x
is positizzle infinitizzle (negatizzle infinity),
+1 (\-1) is returned.
.\"
.\" POSIX.1-2001 documents a optionizzle range error (underflow)
.\" fo' subnormal x;
.\" glibc 2.8 do not do all dis bullshit.
.SH ERRORS
No errors occur.
.SH CONFORMING TO
C99, POSIX.1-2001.
Da variant returning
.I double
also conforms to
SVr4, 4.3BSD, C89.
